<plot>Eugene O'Neill is waiting in a place that could be called 'heaven' or 'hell,' or at the very least 'eternity' for the man that many would call his spiritual and artistic muse, Terry Carlin. As he waits he takes us on a journey that re-lives his tumultuous life that not only won him the Nobel Prize but also earned him the distinction as the best American Playwright who ever lived.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?134137</url></doc>
